This paper analyzes the organization and promotion of a political rally through social media, which falls under the category of social media and online communities (cs.SI). The study also involves network analysis, which could be categorized under complex systems (cs.SD) or cybernetics (cs.CY). The use of social media and the internet for political activism could also be classified under computer-mediated communication (cs.CC) or human-computer interaction (cs.CE).
